<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14168">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Soil%20and%20Water%20Conservation.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8731">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8731 mb-requirement-id-8732">
        (a) Tell what soil is. Tell how it is formed. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.pbs.org/video/soil-video-short-zfxcrn/"
          target="_blank"
          >The Dirt on Soil (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YZ_D1ANF-E0?si=6lNRN2ODpZ7pe872"
          target="_blank"
          >Formation of Soil (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8731 mb-requirement-id-8733">
        (b) Describe three kinds of soil. Tell how they are different. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/G0JcVe_-yu0?si=WuJclD25JrEA4AMg"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of Soil (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8731 mb-requirement-id-8734">
        (c) Name the three main plant nutrients in fertile soil. Tell how they
        can be put back when used up. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zgppw6fJOlw" target="_blank"
          >The Three Most Important Nutrients for Plant Growth (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8735">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8735 mb-requirement-id-8736">
        (a) Define soil erosion. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DRkw5kOZsc8?si=Gq7gY0l0JDMjxhFD"
          target="_blank"
          >Soil Basics: Erosion (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8735 mb-requirement-id-8737">
        (b) Tell why soil erosion is important and how it affects you. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BuEdKEh2buI" target="_blank"
          >Why Soil Conservation is Important to Human Agriculture? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8735 mb-requirement-id-8738">
        (c) Name three kinds of soil erosion. Describe each.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8735 mb-requirement-id-8739">
        (d) Take pictures of or draw two kinds of soil erosion. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://ardasclasses.com/blog/soil-erosion-causes-impacts-and-sustainable-solutions/"
          target="_blank"
          >Soil Erosion: Causes, Impacts, and Sustainable Solutions (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8740">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/YGu_09HH-Xo" target="_blank"
        >What is Soil conservation (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8740 mb-requirement-id-8741">
        (a) Tell what is meant by conservation practices.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8740 mb-requirement-id-8742">
        (b) Describe the effect of three kinds of erosion-control practices.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8740 mb-requirement-id-8743">
        (c) Take pictures of or draw three kinds of erosion-control practices.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://ardasclasses.com/blog/soil-erosion-causes-impacts-and-sustainable-solutions/"
          target="_blank"
          >Soil Erosion: Causes, Impacts and Sustainable Solutions (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8744">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8744 mb-requirement-id-8745">
        (a) Explain what a watershed is. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gVdq4pWUiQM" target="_blank"
          >What is a Water Shed (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ButQspZX2yA?si=TgRhRG8uoKpe4oS3"
          target="_blank"
          >Watersheds, Rivers and Floodplains (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kqwYulqfC9k" target="_blank"
          >How (and Why) to Find Your Watershed (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8744 mb-requirement-id-8746">
        (b) Outline the smallest watershed that you can find on a contour map.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8744 mb-requirement-id-8747">
        (c) Outline, as far as the map will allow, the next larger watershed
        that also has the smallest one in it.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8744 mb-requirement-id-8748">
        (d) Explain what a river basin is. Tell why all people living in a river
        basin should be concerned about land and water use in the basin.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/x7lBi6OaFMo?si=Z2hmQJEjQjmIlQvv"
          target="_blank"
          >River Basins (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8744 mb-requirement-id-8776">
        (e) Explain what an aquifer is and why it can be important to
        communities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/g7R0yLX0V9E" target="_blank"
          >What is an Aquifer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8749">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8749 mb-requirement-id-8750">
        (a) Make a drawing to show the hydrologic cycle. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FzYjPpxP-Cw" target="_blank"
          >The Water (Hydrologic) Cycle (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8749 mb-requirement-id-8751">
        (b) Demonstrate at least two of the following actions of water in
        relation to soil: percolation, capillary action, precipitation,
        evaporation, and transpiration.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5waNTa2b-yg" target="_blank"
          >Capillary Rise (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0Hcp2UGkbj4?si=7U9FAlP5XbSnUVha"
          target="_blank"
          >Soil Capillary Action Demonstration (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CBmDlbFOZKU" target="_blank"
          >Soil Percolation Experiment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8749 mb-requirement-id-8752">
        (c) Explain how removal of vegetation will affect the way water runs off
        a watershed. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wa9MTy_lSpY" target="_blank"
          >How Vegetation Protects Soil (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8749 mb-requirement-id-8753">
        (d) Tell how uses of forest, range, and farmland affect usable water
        supply. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PQf0gdomgGg?si=MNPoiCVV6Cc3QQlQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Rangeland Management and Water Supply (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8749 mb-requirement-id-8754">
        (e) Explain how industrial use affects water supply. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/xeTGV3e1QB8?si=rxKeNygqQnzccQd2"
          target="_blank"
          >Reimagining Industrial Water for Sustainable Impact (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8755">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/4Q8dL8RtQM0" target="_blank"
        >Water Pollution and How We Can Reduce It (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/mgtpMLsAds0" target="_blank"
        >H2-Oh No! Water Pollution 101 (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8755 mb-requirement-id-8756">
        (a) Tell what is meant by water pollution.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8755 mb-requirement-id-8757">
        (b) Describe common sources of water pollution and explain the effects
        of each.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8755 mb-requirement-id-8758">
        (c) Explain the terms: primary water treatment, secondary waste
        treatment, and biochemical oxygen demand. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cUFKay8VPqo" target="_blank"
          >How Does Wastewater Treatment Work? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8755 mb-requirement-id-8759">
        (d) Make a drawing showing the principles of complete waste treatment.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8760">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8761">
        (a) Make a trip to TWO of the following places. Write a report of more
        than 500 words about the soil and water and energy conservation
        practices you saw.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8762">
        (1) An agricultural experiment <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://encyclopediaofalabama.org/article/alabamas-old-rotation-experiment/"
          target="_blank"
          >Alabama's "Old Rotation" Experiment (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8763">
        (2) A managed forest or woodlot, range, or pasture <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1iTvc_8AFVc" target="_blank"
          >Visit to Managed International Paper Forest (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8764">
        (3) A wildlife refuge or a fish or game management area <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/7CynjbXAT24?si=NAvtBGsad_beRE5i"
          target="_blank"
          >Visit to Tennessee National Wildlfe Refuge (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8765">
        (4) A conservation-managed farm or ranch
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8766">
        (5) A managed watershed <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wniaQsuelWs" target="_blank"
          >Watershed Forestry (Massachusetts) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8767">
        (6) A waste-treatment plant <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/P4l-4ehUqhc" target="_blank"
          >How Chicago Cleans 1.4 Billion Gallons Of Wastewater Every Day
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8768">
        (7) A public drinking water treatment plant
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8769">
        (8) An industry water use installation <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qaeXBpag72Q" target="_blank"
          >Water Use in the Paper Industry (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ufJcrXrVaBI" target="_blank"
          >How Data Centers Optimize Energy and Water for Cooling Solutions
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8761 mb-requirement-id-8770">
        (9) A desalinization plant <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/e1pq3Ni7Fko" target="_blank"
          >Carlsbad Desalinization Plant Tour (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8771">
        (b) Plant 100 trees, bushes, and/or vines for a good purpose.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8772">
        (c) Seed an area of at least one-fifth acre for some worthwhile
        conservation purposes, using suitable grasses or legumes alone or in a
        mixture.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8773">
        (d) Study a soil survey report. Describe the things in it. Using tracing
        paper and a pen, trace over any of the soil maps, and outline an area
        with three or more different kinds of soil. List each kind of soil by
        full name and map symbol. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lKFc_96UZ7Q" target="_blank"
          >Web Soil Survey Tutorial (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8774">
        (e) Make a list of places in your neighborhood, camps, school ground, or
        park that have erosion, sedimentation, or pollution problems. Describe
        how these could be corrected through individual or group action.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8760 mb-requirement-id-8775">
        (f) Carry out any other soil and water conservation project approved by
        your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
